value.value: ウォルフ管の退行変性

a retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of the transient embryonic drainage tubes of the embryonic kidney (mesonephric tubules) that empty into the cloaca and later develop into the ductus deferens in the male
ウォルフ管の発達不全

not fully developed or remnants of the transient embryonic drainage tubes of the embryonic kidney (mesonephric tubules) that empty into the cloaca and later develop into the ductus deferens in the male
ミュラー管の発達不全

not fully developed or remnants of the transient embryonic drainage tubes of the embryonic kidney (mesonephric tubules) that empty into the cloaca and in the female develop into the oviducts, uterus, and cranial vagina
頭側膣部の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the upper third of the female reproductive canal located between the uterus and the vulva, usually due to a developmental arrest or agenesis of the caudal Mullerian ducts
副腎過形成
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the adrenal gland, typically resulting in increased size
椎間板脱
extrusion of the cartilaginous and gelatinous structure found between vertebrae
子宮の炎症
local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the uterus
子宮の菲薄化
reduced thickness or depth of the female muscular organ of gestation
子宮嚢胞
presence of one or more fluid-filled sacs inside the lumen of the uterus; usually refers to benign growths
子宮肥大
increase in the bulk size of the female muscular organ of gestation due to cell enlargement
子宮閉塞
presence of a female muscular organ of gestation that ends in a blind segment or sac and does not communicate with the cervix or vagina
子宮角の形態異常
any structural anomaly of either one of the pair of tubular extensions from the uterine body where the uterus and the uterine tubes meet; uterine horns are anterior Mullerian duct-derived structures
子宮角閉塞
presence of a blind-ended segment or pouch at the junction of the uterine horn and the uterine body; the blind horn is typically distended by fluid
子宮角の拡張
an expansion in the volume or area of one or both of the pair of tubular extensions from the uterine body where the uterus and the uterine tubes meet, usually with an increase in contained fluid
子宮角の菲薄化
reduced thickness of either one of the pair of tubular extensions from the uterine body where the uterus and the uterine tubes meet
子宮角の短縮
length reduction or truncation of either one of the pair of tubular extensions from the uterine body where the uterus and the uterine tubes meet
子宮筋層形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the myometrium, typically resulting in decreased size
子宮内膜形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the endometrium, typically resulting in decreased size
子宮内膜過形成
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the endometrium, typically resulting in increased size
卵母細胞の退行変性
a retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of the female germ cells
子宮内膜腺の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the numerous simple or branched tubular glands lined by ciliated columnar epithelium and found in the mucus membrane of the uterus which secrete mucus, lipids, glycogen, and protein; endometrial glands and their secretions (termed histotroph) are critical regulators of peri-implantation embryo survival and implantation as well as establishment of uterine receptivity
子宮内膜腺の数の異常
abnormal number of the simple or branched tubular glands located in the mucous membrane of the uterus
子宮内膜腺の数の減少
fewer than normal numbers of the simple or branched tubular glands found in the mucus membrane of the uterus
子宮内膜腺の欠如
absence of the simple or branched tubular uterine glands
肛門膣瘻
an abnormal anatomical passage that connects the anal canal and the vagina
子宮NK細胞の生理異常

any functional anomaly of a natural killer cell subset that is found in the decidual of the uterus, is CD56-high, Galectin-1-positive and CD16-negative, and is the most abundant immune cell type in the decidual during the first trimester of pregnancy
陰核サイズの異常
anomaly in the size of the small cylindrical erectile body located at the most anterior portion of the vulva
陰核形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the clitoris, typically resulting in decreased size
陰茎亀頭の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the conic expansion of the corpus spongiosum that forms the head of the penis
陰茎骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the unique bone located in the glans penis of most mammals except humans; it is used for copulation and varies in size and shape by species
陰茎骨の矮小化
size reduction or truncation of the unique bone of variable size and shape located in the glans penis of most mammals except humans
陰茎脱
inability to withdraw the penis into the prepuce (the fold of skin covering the glans penis), other than a paraphimosis; not to be confused with phimosis
膵臓のサイズ異常
anomaly in the average size of the organ that secretes pancreatic juice into the duodenum and secretes glucagon and insulin into the bloodstream
膵重量の異常
anomaly in the average weight of the organ that secretes pancreatic juice into the duodenum and secretes glucagon and insulin into the bloodstream
膵重量の増加
increase in the average weight of the organ that secretes pancreatic juice into the duodenum and secretes glucagon and insulin into the bloodstream
膵重量の減少
reduction in the average weight of the organ that secretes pancreatic juice into the duodenum and secretes glucagon and insulin into the bloodstream
膵臓過形成
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the pancrease, typically resulting in increased size
膵臓形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the pancreas, typically resulting in decreased size
膵臓β細胞重量の異常
anomaly in the total physical bulk or volume of a pancreatic beta cell compared to the normal state
膵臓β細胞重量の増加
greater total physical bulk or volume of a pancreatic beta cell compared to the normal state
膵臓β細胞重量の減少
reduced total physical bulk or volume of a pancreatic beta cell compared to the normal state
脂肪細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of a fat-storing cell found mostly in the abdominal cavity and subcutaneous tissue of mammals
褐色脂肪細胞形態異常

any structural anomaly of cells from the thermogenic form of adipose tissue found in newborns of many species, including humans, and in hibernating mammals; brown fat is capable of rapid liberation of energy and seems to be important in the maintenance of body temperature immediately after birth and upon waking from hibernation; brown adipocytes contain multiple small droplets of triglycerides and a high number of mitochondria
白色脂肪細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of fat cells with light coloration and few mitochondria; these contain a scant ring of cytoplasm surrounding a single large lipid droplet or vacuole
白色脂肪細胞サイズの増加
increase in the size of fat cells with light coloration and few mitochondria
褐色脂肪細胞サイズの増加
increase in the size of fat cells from the thermogenic form of adipose tissue
